<worksheet>
  <title>Homework Assignment #7 - Math 122</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      <alert>Due Sunday, 11/8</alert>
    </p>
    <p>
      These are the requirements for all homework assignments.
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            On all problems, you must show all work necessary to justify your solution.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            On all problems, you must find a way to explain your reasoning.  You must do this in complete sentences.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            In your explanations and supporting work, do your best to demonstrate your understanding of the problem and the concepts used to solve them.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Make sure you carefully check the accuracy of your computations.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      You may turn in your assignment as a hard copy in class, or you may submit your assignment electronically on Blackboard.  <alert>If you turn in your assignment electronically, you <em>must</em> convert it to a PDF file.</alert>.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <p>
    Here are the problems for this assignment. Do not use any formulas that you cannot justify.
  </p>

  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        (70 pts.) Jojo has credit card debt of $1000.  The card has an annual interest rate of 18% compounded every month, with a minimum monthly payment of $20.  When a payment is made, the interest is computed before the payment is applied to the balance.
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              Determine Jojo's balance after 6 months if they always make the minimum monthly payment.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Determine Jojo's balance after 6 months if they pay $40 per month.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Compare the amount of money that Jojo paid in #1 and #2, and compare that to the difference in the amount of Jojo's debt that was paid off in #1 and #2.  Briefly discuss anything that seemed disproportionate between the difference in payment versus the difference in debt paid off (i.e. did one of those differences seem proportionately smaller than the other?).
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Determine Jojo's balance after 6 months if they pay $<m>x</m> per month.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Use your answer to #4 to determine how much Jojo's monthly payment must be to pay off their debt in 6 months.  Hint:  What should your answer to \#4 be equal to?
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Now suppose Jojo has credit card debt of $<m>A</m> with an annual interest rate of <m>r</m>, compounded every month.  Find a formula for how much Jojo's monthly payment needs to be in order to pay their debt off in 6 months.  Show all work.  I suggest using the same reasoning as you did in #5.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <exercise>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Collaboration Reflection (5 pts.):  For each of the following, write a 2-4 sentence reflection related to your collaboration with your group.  You may write about positive contributions made and/or ways that contributions could be improved.
        <ul>
          <li>
            <p>
              Write a reflection on your contributions to the collaboration.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Write a reflection about your fellow collaborators' contributions.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
        You will not be penalized for any shortcomings you or your fellow group members had in your collaboration.  Any good-faith effort you make to think about and explain your collaboration experience will be rewarded.  I also will not share your reflections with anyone else in your group or the rest of the class without your permission.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>

  <p>
    If you want to read about some different ways of being a good collaborator, click on <url href="">this rubric</url> for some ideas.  I will not be grading you according to how well you do on this rubric, only on how you reflect about your collaboration.
  </p>

</worksheet>